## Key Takeaways

- SSH is the standard way to access remote Linux machines — you'll use it in every level.
- Ports matter. Default SSH = port 22. Always check if a service uses a non-standard port.
- When a password field shows nothing as you type, that's intentional — type normally and press Enter.

